other_tests.procedure_name: CT abdomen and pelvis with contrast
other_tests.findings: Appendix is enlarged measuring up to 10 mm with apparent mural thickening and mucosal hyperemia. Adjacent fat stranding noted. There are least 2 adjacent cecal diverticula, 1 of which appears inflamed and positioned adjacent to the appendix. Adjacent free air locules seen abutting the inflamed diverticulum. Multiple prominent adjacent lymph nodes are likely reactive in nature.
